rces in the arena (buffers, rule structures, etc.). If the error recovery doesn't properly clean up or if the newer bison parser's error handling is different, this can lead to inconsistent arena state.\n\n\nThe yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1 function in parser.c triggers YYERROR when it detects a duplicate identifier, but by that point the arena has already been modified by earlier operations. I need to trace where in the grammar this phase 1 reduction gets invoked to understand the sequence of allocations.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31357,"cache_read_input_tokens":60659,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31357},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3854-61c7-4e43-9684-8fe847acdab5","uuid":"057186d1-df35-4de1-9f66-b31b4ce89be5"}
