{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HjtekqonrpkRA3jsyB5vz7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So lines 318-320 show the error recovery rules. These are `rules error rule`, `rules error import`, and `rules error \"include\"`. These allow the parser to skip errors and continue parsing.\n\nNow the key issue is: when an error occurs during parsing \"rule test rule test\", what happens?\n\n1. The parser starts parsing \"rule test\"\n2. It matches `rule_modifiers _RULE_ _IDENTIFIER_` and calls `yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1`\n3. This function allocates a YR_RULE structure in the arena and increments compiler->next_rule_idx\n4. The parser expects `{` next but sees `_RULE_` instead, causing a syntax error\n5. The parser enters error recovery and matches `rules error rule`\n6. After the error recovery, the parser tries to match `rule` again\n7. It matches `rule_modifiers _RULE_ _IDENTIFIER_` again with the second \"rule test\"\n8. It calls `yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1` again\n9. This time, when the function checks if \"test\" already exists as a rule, it detects the duplicate and returns ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER\n\nThe problem is that after step 3, the arena has been modified and compiler->next_rule_idx has been incremented, but the rule was never completed (phase 2 wasn't called). When we then allocate another rule in step 9, the arena state is inconsistent.\n\nHowever, this should have been a problem even with bison 3.0.5. Unless... the newer bison version changes HOW the error recovery works or WHEN it happens.\n\nLet me check the actual output of the failing test case to see what's going on. Let me check if there's a specific issue with error recovery and destructors.\n\nActually, looking at the grammar.y file again, I noticed there are %destructor declarations at lines 267-278. \n\nThe %destructor rules are meant to clean up values when they're discarded during error recovery. These might have changed in how they're generated in the newer bison version, potentially affecting when and how cleanup happens during error handling.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":519,"cache_read_input_tokens":100224,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":519},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3854-61c7-4e43-9684-8fe847acdab5","uuid":"af1c7008-e670-459c-8123-9a9417a74373"}
