{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_012HtboUwdEcVCFrMiBXq9JD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Aha! This is very important! The original fix for issue #1295 moved the lines:\n```c\n  compiler->current_rule_idx = compiler->next_rule_idx;\n  compiler->next_rule_idx++;\n```\n\nfrom near the beginning of the function (right after getting the compiler from yyscanner) to AFTER the duplicate check.\n\nThis is because the duplicate check needs to happen BEFORE incrementing the rule index. Otherwise, if the duplicate is detected, the indices have already been incremented, leaving the compiler in an inconsistent state.\n\nBut looking at the current code in parser.c at line 855-856:\n```c\n  compiler->current_rule_idx = compiler->next_rule_idx;\n  compiler->next_rule_idx++;\n```\n\nThis is BEFORE the duplicate check at line 863-870. This means the current code has the BUGGY version, not the fixed version!\n\nSo the problem is: the fix for #1295 (commit bb42569d) moved these lines to AFTER the duplicate check (after line 870), but the current code has them BEFORE the duplicate check.\n\nThis suggests that the generated grammar files have reverted this fix, or the parser.c file was not properly updated when the grammar was regenerated.\n\nLet me verify where these lines currently are in the buggy parser.c.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":751,"cache_read_input_tokens":101951,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":751},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3854-61c7-4e43-9684-8fe847acdab5","uuid":"c9f21e2f-165e-4b38-b615-cc4dcdd6c3a0"}
